      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "I don't see the harm in leaving this? It could be that it's possible to compile certain parts of the code as c++14, but we want to document through code that c++17 is THE supported standard.\r\n\r\nFor ex, I have no idea, but it may currently be possible (or possible soon, after the next refactors) to build an app using libbitcoinkernel's headers in c++14 mode. If that's the case, we want to force that to be an error.",
